This section, a roster of the individuals who gathered in Washington to debate, legislate, and occasionally brawl, is arranged by chamber, then by state. [Senators](/United_States_Senate) are listed in order of seniority, a system that, one presumes, was meant to instill some semblance of order, while [representatives](/United_States_House_of_Representatives) are listed by district. One can almost picture the sheer volume of personalities, ambitions, and conflicting ideologies crammed into the hallowed halls of the [United States Capitol](/United_States_Capitol) during these fraught years.

